leads.lead_text: Plants prostrate to erect; leaves mostly more than 4 times longer than wide, some usually with small subapical teeth; fruiting pedicels decurved; seeds deeply wrinkled; lowlands or low mountain areas, rarely subalpine
Plants quite prostrate; leaves less than 4 times longer than wide, entire; fruiting pedicels erect or decurved; seeds smooth or obscurely wrinkled; alpine and subalpine
